  "firstAcquaintance": "A mysterious magical tool maker. Most people know of her existence, but very few have ever seen her true face.",
  "personality": "Loves teasing people she finds interesting. Completely ignores anything she does not care about.",
  "like": "Alchemy tools, history books, blueberry milkshakes",
  "familiarData": "Miacosis, an alchemist from an ancient family. She was adopted by a magical family since she was self-aware and grew up in a magic tower, so there is no trace of minotaur tribal wildness about her. Instead, she exudes refinement and mystery.\nMiacosis is fortunate. As a half-breed, she never faced discrimination. In fact, her horns resemble demon horns, which earned her respect and awe. This lucky life inspired her to share her good fortune with others, so she became a magical tool maker, crafting simple and practical magical devices for her customers.\nMagical tools are so convenient that factions often fight over them, but she personally does not care and has no interest in joining any faction. However, this means she has to relocate her workshop from time to time.\nMages tend to have messy rooms, but you would never see that in Miacosis. She is excellent at organizing and very skilled at using limited space to store a vast amount of things. This is reflected in her outfit as well -- despite wearing simple clothing, she can pull out all kinds of magical tools.\nAs for how much she actually keeps hidden in her cleavage? Nobody knows.",
